==English==
===Noun phrase===
[[Image:Triangle.Right.svg|thumb|right|A right triangle.]]
'''right triangle''' (''plural'' '''right triangles''')

#A [[triangle]] having a [[right angle]] as one of its interior angles.

====Synonyms====
*[[right-angled triangle]] (''see usage note below'')

====Usage note====
'''Right triangle''' is probably the more common term in the US, while 
'''right-angled triangle''' is probably the more common term in the UK,

